An angry mob on Thursday burnt to death a suspected cultists who was found in the process of butchering the body of a lady after killing her. The incident happened at the Akenfa area of Yenagoa the Bayelsa state capital. It was learnt that he was caught while trying to cut open the body of the young lady identified as Best, an indigene of Epie, when luck ran out of him and was apprehended by the mob. Eyewitnesses said the angry mob were angered that the man challenged them with the axe he used for his nefarious activities and threatened to kill again. Community sources said the man who is well known in the community behaved like a mad man in the day time but have been killing people at night, especially women. The source said the late Best, was his latest victim as three other ladies have lost their lives in the same circumstances in the last one month.